

VxSpinButton(1vtcl)                           VxSpinButton(1vtcl)

SSyynnooppssiiss
       VxSpinButton widget width lower underCB upper overCB \
       increment default userCB position upOp dnOP

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       Creates  a  SpinButton  called widget, which consists of a
       text field and two buttons which increase and decrease the
       numeric  value  in  the  text field within upper and lower
       bounds.

   AArrgguummeennttss
       All arguments to VxSpinButton except  upOp  and  dnOp  are
       mandatory.  Arguments  may  be specified as blank strings,
       and must appear in this order: The name of the  SpinButton
       widget.   The  width, in columns, of the text component of
       the SpinButton.  The lower boundary value.  A callback for
       when  the  value  goes  below  the lower bound.  If set to
       "``'', the package automatically wraps the value around to
       the  upper  value.   The upper boundary value.  A callback
       for when the value goes over the upper bound.  If  set  to
       ``'',  the package automatically wraps the value around to
       the lower value.  Sets how much  the  value  increases  or
       decreases  each  time  the button is pressed.  The initial
       default value.  A callback which validates  the  value  of
       the  text component of the SpinButton. Specify ``'' for no
       callback.  A list containing any  geometry  arguments  for
       the  SpinButton.   Optional operation to perform on incre-
       ment when the ``up'' button is pressed (+ if not present).
       Optional  operation  to  perform  on  increment  when  the
       ``down'' button is pressed (- if not present).

   GGlloobbaallss
       array of lower boundary values, indexed by widget.   array
       of upper boundary values, indexed by widget.

RReettuurrnn vvaalluueess
       If  successful,  the VxSpinButton command returns the name
       of the enclosing form widget (the name of  the  SpinButton
       widget).

EExxaammpplleess
       proc  CreateSpin {form} {      set spin [VxSpinButton spin
       15 0 "" 100 "" 2 50 "" "" + -]

            # widget name = spin      # width = 15       #  lower
       bound  = 0      # lower callback = blank ("")      # upper
       bound = 100      # upper  callback  =  blank  ("")       #
       increment  = 2      # default value = 50      # user call-
       back = blank ("")      # position = blank ("")       #  up
       operation = + (default, may be omitted)      # down opera-
       tion = - (default, may be omitted)      }

       set app [VtOpen Spin]

